Name: Animating Breaths
Description: Instead of using your Breath Weapon, you may instead spend 4 uses of it to summon an Animated Breath (FTD) related to your Chromatic ancestry. The Animated Breath is under your control and you can command it (no action required). It remains for 10 minutes.

Name: Ruthless Fire
Description: You gain the benefits of the Graze Orenth trait. Additionally, before you attack a creature you may reduce your hit bonus by a value of your choosing. If you hit you deal twice this value in fire damage to the target.

Name: Master Fey Steps
Description: You have mastered your Fey Steps Feature. You get a teleport speed equal to your walking speed.

Name: Advanced Photosynthesis
Description: Your Photosynthesis Trait functions whenever you are in bright light.

Name: Slowed Time Strikes
Description: You gain the benefits of the Slow Orenth trait. However, instead of reducing their speed by 10 feet you may instead choose to give them the Dazed condition.

Name: Weapon Mastered: Vex
Description: After you use your Vex Orenth Trait you can choose to make an additional attack against them instead of gaining advantage. You may do so once per turn.

Name: Dragon Turtle Speed
Description: You gain the benefits of the Slow Orenth trait. However, instead of reducing their speed by 10 feet you may instead choose to give them the Slowed condition.

Name: Human Variety
Description: The variety of humans leads to them being able to accomplish extraordinary feats. You gain a feat.

Name: School Mastered: Evocation
Prerequisite: Spell mastery with an Evocation school spell.
Description: You may downcast any Evocation spell that can be upcast of 2nd level or higher. When you do so reduce the number of damage dice in the same pattern as it gets increased for higher level spellslots.

Name: Mighty Recovery
Description: Choose a tier 1 Orenth trait that gives you a first level spellslot back. You may instead get a fith level spellslot back. The orenth type of this trait is the same as the tier 1 trait you choose.  You cannot choose the same tier 1 trait in this way twice.
